Eastern Cape police have opened an attempted murder case after a University of Fort Hare employee was found  bound and gagged in his flat. The alarm was raised when the 32-year-old did not report  for work on Wednesday, said police spokesperson Brig Tembinkosi Kinana. His colleagues went to his  flat in Alice, where they found him. “The circumstances surrounding the incident are  under investigation. No injuries were reported. No arrest [has yet been] made.” Kinana said  police “do not relate or associate this incident with previous incidents  reported and associated with Fort Hare University employees”. Police have asked anyone with information to contact the Alice police station or Crime Stop on 08600-10111. TimesLIVE Support independent journalism by subscribing to the Sunday Times. Just R20 for the first month.